    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-16T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-16T14:00:00-05:00" n="532"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d532">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">103.9169/4120d: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-16T15:00:00-04:00"
                            >June 16, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1206. Your 1856 of May 24, 1591 of May 5, and 1352 of April 19. Department and
                    FEA are gratified that the Swedes have taken steps to end shipment of coal to
                    Norway via Bothnian route. However, we still wish to obtain if possible the
                    limitations requested in your <hi rend="italic">aide-mémoire</hi> of May 5 (your
                    1591 and 1352). Please continue to make every effort to achieve our objective at
                    an early date. The procedure <pb facs="0579" n="569" xml:id="pg_569"/> to be
                    used is left to your discretion. This telegram is being repeated to London and
                    the British Embassy here is telegraphing London so that your British colleague
                    will receive parallel instructions.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
